item.description:
Fan invades Field with a knife and hits Player - Blooming (Bol) vs River Plate (Uru) (AMAZING)
Torcedor Invade campo com uma faca na mão - 11.08.2009 - BOLIVIA VS URUGUAI GUERRA A partida entre Blooming-BOL e River Plate-URU, no estádio de Santa Cruz de la Sierra, na Bolívia, pela fase preliminar da Copa Sul-Americana, foi interrompida e suspensa pelo árbitro Victor Hugo Carrillo, aos 20 minutos do segundo tempo, após um torcedor invadir o gramado e agredir o jogador Henry Gimenez, do time uruguaio. De acordo com a imprensa local, o invasor, que foi preso, estaria portando uma faca. Os visitantes venciam por 1 a 0, e o incidente aconteceu logo após o gol de Frederico Puppo, que aproveitou a falha do goleiro para marcar. "The match between Blooming-BOL-URU and River Plate, at the Santa Cruz de la Sierra, Bolivia, the preliminary phase of the Copa Sul-Americana, was interrupted and suspended by the referee Victor Hugo Carrillo, 20 minutes for the second time, after a fan invaded the pitch and attacking the player Henry Gimenez, the Uruguayan team. According to local press, the attacker, who was arrested, was carrying a knife. Visitors due by 1 to 0, and the incident happened after the goal of John Puppo, who took the failure of the goalkeeper to score. With the decision of the arbitration to stop the game, and red objects were thrown into the lawn." Com a decisão da arbitragem de interromper o jogo, objetos e rojões foram lançados ao gramado.

item.title: HatingnotDebating
item.description:
HatingnotDebating
This is what actually happened at the event. The news only showed the woman being escorted away by the police. What happened was the women walked in with signs, the crowd booed and yelled at the women. The women rolled up their posters and put them down. A photographer/reporter approached the woman on the end and wanted to see what the poster was. As the woman went to show the photographer/reporter what the poster was, a man from the bleachers stood up and snatched the poster from the woman and photographer/reporter. As the woman went to retrieve her poster the police stepped in and escorted the woman and the man from the building. The poster was not of Obama, it was not pro health care, the poster that was taken from the woman and wrinkled up into a ball was of Rosa Parks. National news coverage only showed the woman being escorted from the forum and left out the fact that it was the man who started the incident. Not to mention it was a poster of Rosa Parks.
